                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Model Logic: Why MLP?</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">
                        While Random Forest offers a strong baseline, we utilize a <strong>Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP)</strong> as the primary target. Gradient-based attacks (like FGSM) require the differentiable loss surface provided by Neural Networks.
                    </p>
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-8">
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-slate-200">
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-tech-primary">Random Forest</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-1">Non-differentiable. Robust baseline. Harder to attack with gradients.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-slate-200">
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-tech-danger">MLP (Neural Net)</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-1">Differentiable. Susceptible to gradient descent attacks (FGSM/PGD).</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 3. The Attack Section -->
        <section id="attacks">
            <div class="text-center mb-10">
                <span class="inline-block py-1 px-3 rounded-full bg-tech-danger/10 text-tech-danger font-bold text-sm mb-4">THREAT MODEL</span>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">The Evasion Attack</h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
                    Adversarial attacks modify malicious packets just enough to cross the classifier's decision boundary. By adding a small perturbation ($\epsilon$), typically invisible to human operators, the NIDS is tricked into classifying attacks as benign traffic.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <!-- Plotly 3D Visualization -->
